Class CommandEngine

    ICommandEngine, net.dv8tion.jda.api.hooks.EventListener

    public class CommandEngine
extends net.dv8tion.jda.api.hooks.ListenerAdapter
implements ICommandEngine
    The core of commando4j, It will handle all command calls registered through this engine.

    • Constructor Detail

      • CommandEngine

        protected CommandEngine()
        Creates an Instance of this ICommandEngine implementations. It will initialize a SQLite database if the Repository implementation is set as the IRepository implementation for the Engine (preset by default). You may change it by using setRepository(IRepository) method.

      • setInstance

        public static void setInstance(ICommandEngine newCommandConfig)
        Set a custom implementation of ICommandEngine. It if highly recommended that to customize the engine, you extend from the default implementation CommandEngine instead of a raw version.

        By default, CommandEngine implementation will be used.

        Parameters:
        newCommandConfig - custom implementation of ICommandEngine

      • includeBuildInUtils

        public static void includeBuildInUtils()
        Include pre-created commands, such has Help, Ping, Language and prefix.

        Help: command to get simple and detailed information about commands.

        Ping: Test to see if the bot is reachable.

        Language: Set the language used in a guild.

        prefix: Set the prefix the bot react to in a guild.

        • NOTE: To include only some of these command, use ICommandEngine.addCommand(ICommand) instead.
        See Also:
        HelpCommand, PrefixCommand, LanguageCommand, PrefixCommand
